Aker Philadelphia Gets NK1B in Aker Loans, Finansavisen Says

-- B y   M e e r a   B h a t i a
-- 
2011-04-30T10:27:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-30/aker-philadelphia-gets-nk1b-in-aker-loans-finansavisen-says.html
Aker Philadelphia Shipyards ASA
will focus on finishing the construction of two ships it got
funding for and will then look to win new contracts,
Finansavisen reported, citing Kristian Roekke, who took over as
chief executive officer this month.  Aker ASA (AKER) ’s chairman and Kristian Roekke’s father, Kjell
Inge Roekke, has given his son 1 billion kroner in loans and
guarantees from Aker, which owns 71.2 percent of the yard, the
Oslo-based newspaper reported today.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
